Every resident of Kalmykia is a debtor
Residents of the republic are increasingly visiting the official website of the Office of the Federal Bailiff Service of Russia for the Republic of Kazakhstan.
According to the specialists of the department of organizational and control work, informatization and information security of the republican department, over the past eight months, more than 140 thousand visits to the site itself were registered, more than 42 thousand - the section "Bank of data of enforcement proceedings," downloaded 661 payment receipts for payment of debts.
According to the Chairman of the Public Council under the UFSSP of Russia for the Republic of Kazakhstan Valery Bogdanov, almost every resident of the region are charged with debts for utility payments, traffic police fines, bank loans, loans, and no one is insured against unforeseen situations.
But debtors can wait for negative consequences in the form, for example, of a ban on traveling abroad.
That is why the UFSSP of Russia in the Republic of Kazakhstan recommends to all those who have planned a trip abroad to clarify in the bailiffs department at the place of residence or on the website www.r08fssprus.ru information about the presence of unpaid debts and repay them.
The service created the "Bank of data of enforcement proceedings" for the convenience of citizens.
This special electronic application is not only on the regional sites of the UFSSP of Russia, but also in social networks and mobile communications iPad, iPhone and smartphone.
The data bank contains information on enforcement proceedings initiated by the Kalmyk bailiffs against all debtors, - explains the assistant head of the UFSSP of Russia for the Republic of Kazakhstan Delgyr Bodgayev.
"In the presence of arrears, the system displays information about the number and date of initiation of enforcement proceedings; the name of the body that issued the executive sheet or other act; its numbers, amount and form of debt; the address of the bailiff; the full name of the bailiff;
Information on the progress of enforcement proceedings can also be obtained on the portal of public services at: http://epgu.gosuslugi.ru"
